The paper presents a clustering algorithm based on Gaussian mixture model, which is a common technique in machine learning and data analysis. The focus of the paper is on hierarchical clustering, which is a subfield of clustering and can be applied to various domains such as computer vision (cs.CV), natural language processing (cs.CL), and social network analysis (cs.SI). The paper also discusses the ability of the proposed method in noise detection, which is a common problem in machine learning and data analysis. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CV (Computer Vision), cs.CL (Computation and Language), and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
